msgstr "2 --- Ponto"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3462
msgid "**Output geometry has z values**"
msgstr "**A geometria de saída tem valores z**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3463
msgid "``WITH_Z``"
msgstr "``WITH_Z``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3467
msgid "Choose if the output geometry should include the Z dimension"
msgstr "Escolha se a geometria de saída deve incluir a dimensão de ."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3468
msgid "**Output geometry has m values**"
msgstr "**Output geometry has m values**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3469
msgid "``WITH_M``"
msgstr "``WITH_M``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3473
msgid "Choose if the output geometry should include the M dimension"
msgstr "Escolha se a geometria de saída deva incluir a dimensão M."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3474
msgid "**Geometry expression**"
msgstr "**Expressão geométrica**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3475
msgid "``EXPRESSION``"
msgstr "``EXPRESSION``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3476
msgid "[expression]"
msgstr "[expressão]"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3478
msgid "Default: '$geometry'"
msgstr "Padrão: '$geometria'"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3479
msgid ""
"Add the geometry expression you want to use. You can use the button to open "
"the Expression Dialog. The dialog lists all the relevant expressions, "
"together with their help and guide."
msgstr ""
"Adicione a geometria que você queira usa. Você pode usar o botão para abrir "
"a expressão Diálogo. O diálogo lista todas as expressão relevantes, juntas "
"com a sua ajuda e guia."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3483
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3506
msgid "**Modified geometry**"
msgstr "**Geometria modificada**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3514
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:geometrybyexpression``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:geometrybyexpression``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3524
msgid "Interpolate point on line"
msgstr "Interpolar ponto na linha"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3525
msgid ""
"Creates a point geometry interpolated at a set distance along line or curve "
"geometries."
msgstr ""
"Cria uma geometria de ponto interpolada a uma distância definida ao longo de"
" geometrias de linha ou curva."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3528
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3689
msgid "Z and M values are linearly interpolated from existing values."
msgstr ""
"Os valores Z e M são interpolados linearmente a partir dos valores "
"existentes."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3530
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3691
msgid ""
"If a multipart geometry is encountered, only the first part is considered "
"when calculating the substring."
msgstr ""
"Se uma geometria com várias partes é encontrada, somente a primeira parte é "
"considerada quando calculando a substring."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3533
msgid ""
"If the specified distance is greater than the input feature's length, the "
"resultant feature will have a null geometry."
msgstr ""
"Se a distância especificada for maior que o tamanho da entrada, o resultado "
"da característica será uma geometria nula."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3539
msgid "Interpolated point at 500m of the beginning of the line"
msgstr "Ponto interpolado a 500m do início da linha"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3541
msgid ":ref:`qgispointsalonglines`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgispointsalonglines`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3564
msgid "Distance from the beginning of the line"
msgstr "Distância do início da linha"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3565
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3588
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4703
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4726
msgid "**Interpolated points**"
msgstr "**Pontos interpolados**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3591
msgid ""
"The output point vector layer with features at a set distance along the line"
" or polygon boundary"
msgstr ""
"O ponto de camada de saída vetorizada com as características em uma certa "
"distância junto com a linha ou o limite do polígono."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3597
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:interpolatepoint``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:interpolatepoint``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3607
msgid "Keep N biggest parts"
msgstr "Mantenha N partes maiores"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3608
msgid ""
"Takes a layer with polygons or multipolygons and returns a new layer in "
"which only the *n* largest polygons of each multipolygon feature are kept. "
"If a feature has *n* or fewer parts, the feature will just be copied."
msgstr ""
"Pegue uma camada com polígonos ou multipoligonal e retorne uma nova camada "
"na qual somente *n* polígonos largos de cada característica multipoligonal "
"são mantidos. Se a característica tem *n* ou menos partes, a característica "
"somente será copiada.  "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3616
msgid ""
"Clockwise from top left: original multipart feature, one, two and three "
"biggest parts kept"
msgstr ""
"Sentido horário campo superior esquerdo: Característica com várias, uma, "
"duas ou três partes maiores mantidas."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3631
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3801
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3824
msgid "**Polygons**"
msgstr "**Polígonos**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3635
msgid "**Parts to keep**"
msgstr "**Parts to keep**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3636
msgid "``PARTS``"
msgstr "``PARTS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3640
msgid ""
"Number of parts to keep. If 1, only the biggest part of the feature will be "
"kept."
msgstr ""
"Número de partes para se manter. Se 1, somente a parte maior da "
"característica será mantida."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3642
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3665
msgid "**Parts**"
msgstr "**Partes**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3668
msgid ""
"The output polygon vector layer with the N biggest parts of each feature"
msgstr ""
"A camada vetorial de saída poligonal com a N partes maiores de cada "
"característica."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3684
msgid "Line substring"
msgstr "Linha de substring."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3685
msgid ""
"Returns the portion of a line (or curve) which falls between the specified "
"start and end distances (measured from the beginning of the line)."
msgstr ""
"Retorna a porção da linha (curva) que pode fica o início especificado e o ao"
" final das distâncias (mesurado a partir do começo das linhas)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3697
msgid ""
"Substring line with starting distance set at 0 meters and the ending "
"distance at 250 meters."
msgstr "Linha de substring com começo posto em 0 metros e final 250 metros. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3703
msgid ":ref:`qgisextendlines`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisextendlines`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3726
msgid "Distance along the input line to the start point of the output feature"
msgstr ""
"Distância ao longo da linha de entrada até o ponto inicial do recurso de "
"saída."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3732
msgid "Distance along the input line to the end point of the output feature"
msgstr ""
"Distância ao longo da linha de entrada até o ponto final da feição de saída"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3733
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3756
msgid "**Substring**"
msgstr "**Sub-cadeia**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3759
msgid "The output line vector layer."
msgstr "Camada vetorial da linha de saída."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3764
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:linesubstring``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:linesubstring``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3774
msgid "Lines to polygons"
msgstr "Linhas para polígonos"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3775
msgid ""
"Generates a polygon layer using as polygon rings the lines from an input "
"line layer."
msgstr ""
"Gera uma camada de polígono usando como anéis de polígono as linhas de uma "
"camada de linha de entrada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3783
msgid ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3832
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:linestopolygons``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:linestopolygons``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3842
msgid "Merge lines"
msgstr "Mesclar linhas"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3843
msgid ""
"Joins all connected parts of MultiLineString geometries into single "
"LineString geometries."
msgstr ""
"Junta todas as partes conectadas das geometrias MultiLineString em somente "
"uma do tipo de geometrias de LineString."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3846
msgid ""
"If any parts of the input MultiLineString geometries are not connected, the "
"resultant geometry will be a MultiLineString containing any lines which "
"could be merged and any non-connected line parts."
msgstr ""
"Se quaisquer partes da entrada das geometrias MultiLineString não são "
"conectadas, a geometria resultante será uma MultiLineString contendendo "
"qualquer linha que pode ser mesclada e qualquer linha não conectada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3870
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3893
msgid "**Merged**"
msgstr "**Mesclado**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3896
msgid "The output (merged) line vector layer."
msgstr "A saída (mesclada) de linha de camada vetorial "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3901
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:mergelines``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:mergelines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3911
msgid "Minimum bounding geometry"
msgstr "Geometria minimamente limitada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3912
msgid ""
"Creates geometries which enclose the features from an input layer. The "
"features can be grouped by a field. The output layer will then contain one "
"feature per group value with a geometry (MBB) that covers the geometries of "
"the features with matching value."
msgstr ""
"Cria geometrias que podem incluir características de uma camada inserida. As"
" características podem ser agrupadas por campo. A camada de saída conterá "
"uma característica por valor de grupo com a geometria (MBB) que cobre as "
"geometrias das características com valores que coincidem. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3918
msgid "The following enclosing geometry types are supported:"
msgstr "As seguintes tipos de geometrias são suportadas:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3920
msgid "bounding box (envelope)"
msgstr "caixa delimitadora (envelope)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3921
msgid "oriented rectangle"
msgstr "retângulo orientado"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3922
msgid "circle"
msgstr "círculo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3923
msgid "convex hull"
msgstr "Casca convexa (convex hull)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3928
msgid ""
"Clockwise from top left: envelope, oriented rectangle, circle, convex hull"
msgstr ""
"Sentido horário a partir do campo superior esquerdo: envelope, retângulo "
"orientado, círculo e casca convexa."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3931
msgid ":ref:`qgisminimumenclosingcircle`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisminimumenclosingcircle`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3949
msgid "**Field**"
msgstr "**Campo**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3954
msgid ""
"Features can be grouped by a field. If set, this causes the output layer to "
"contain one feature per grouped value with a minimal geometry covering only "
"the features with matching values."
msgstr ""
"Características podem ser agrupadas por campo. Se configurado, isso faz com "
"que a camada de saída contenha uma característica por valor de grupo com uma"
" mínima geometria cobrindo somente as características que se coincidem. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3958
msgid "**Geometry type**"
msgstr "**Tipo de Geometria**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3963
msgid "Enclosing geometry types. One of:"
msgstr "Tipos de geometrias fechadas. Uma do tipo:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3965
msgid "0 --- Envelope (Bounding Box)"
msgstr "0 --- Envelope (Caixa limitante)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3966
msgid "1 --- Minimum Oriented Rectangle"
msgstr "1 --- Retângulo Orientado Mínimo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3967
msgid "2 --- Minimum Enclosing Circle"
msgstr "2 --- Círculo Fechado Mínimo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3968
msgid "3 --- Convex Hull"
msgstr "3 --- Casca convexa "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3970
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3993
msgid "**Bounding geometry**"
msgstr "Geometria Limitante."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4009
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:minimumboundinggeometry``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:minimumboundinggeometry``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4019
msgid "Minimum enclosing circles"
msgstr "Círculos mínimos fechados. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4020
msgid ""
"Calculates the minimum enclosing circles of the features in the input layer."
msgstr ""
"Calcula o fechamento mínimo dos círculos das características na camada de "
"entrada. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4026
msgid "Enclosing circles for each feature"
msgstr "Círculos fechados para cada característica."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4054
msgid "Default: 72"
msgstr "Padrão: 72"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4057
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4080
msgid "**Minimum enclosing circles**"
msgstr "**Minimum enclosing circles**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4091
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:minimumenclosingcircle``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:minimumenclosingcircle``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4101
msgid "Multi-ring buffer (constant distance)"
msgstr "Buffer de multi anéis (distância constante)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4102
msgid ""
"Computes multi-ring (*donut*) buffer for the features of the input layer, "
"using a fixed or dynamic distance and number of rings."
msgstr ""
"Computa buffer de multi anéis (*donut*) para as características da camada de"
" entrada, usando uma distância fixa ou dinâmica  e números de anéis."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4108
msgid "Multi-ring buffer for a line, point and polygon layer"
msgstr "Buffer de multi anéis para uma linha, ponto ou camada poligonal."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4117
msgid ""
":ref:`qgisbuffer`, :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`, "
":ref:`qgisrectanglesovalsdiamonds`, :ref:`qgissinglesidedbuffer`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgisbuffer`, :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`, "
":ref:`qgisrectanglesovalsdiamonds`, :ref:`qgissinglesidedbuffer`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4136
msgid "**Number of rings**"
msgstr "**Número de anéis**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4137
msgid "``RINGS``"
msgstr "``RINGS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4141
msgid ""
"The number of rings. It can be a unique value (same number of rings for all "
"the features) or it can be taken from features data (the number of rings "
"depends on feature values)."
msgstr ""
"O número de anéis. Pode ser um valor único (mesmo número de anéis para todas"
" as características) ou pode ser pego por características de data (o número "
"de anéis depende dos valores das características)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4145
msgid "**Distance between rings**"
msgstr "**Distância entre anéis**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4150
msgid ""
"Distance between the rings. It can be a unique value (same distance for all "
"the features) or it can be taken from features data (the distance depends on"
" feature values)."
msgstr ""
"A distância entre os anéis. Pode ser um valor único (mesma distância para "
"todas as características) ou pode ser trazido dos dados das características "
"(a distância depende do valores da característica)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4154
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4177
msgid "**Multi-ring buffer (constant distance)**"
msgstr "**Buffer de multi anéis (distância constante)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4187
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiringconstantbuffer``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiringconstantbuffer``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4197
msgid "Multipart to singleparts"
msgstr "Multipartes para partes únicas."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4198
msgid "Splits multipart features in the input layer into singlepart features."
msgstr ""
"Separa características multipartidárias na camada de entrada em "
"características únicas."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4201
msgid ""
"The attributes of the output layer are the same as the original ones but "
"divided into single features."
msgstr ""
"Os atributos da camada de saída são os mesmos que os originais, mas "
"divididos em feições únicas."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4207
msgid ""
"Left the multipart source layer and right the single part output result"
msgstr ""
"Esquerda da camada fonte multipartidária e o resultado de parte única de "
"saída à direita ."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4219
msgid ":ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgispromotetomulti`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgispromotetomulti`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4237
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4260
msgid "**Single parts**"
msgstr "**Partes individuais**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4263
msgid "The output vector layer."
msgstr "A camada vetorial de saída."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4268
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiparttosingleparts``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiparttosingleparts``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4278
msgid "Offset lines"
msgstr "Linhas de desvio."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4279
msgid ""
"Offsets lines by a specified distance. Positive distances will offset lines "
"to the left, and negative distances will offset them to the right."
msgstr ""
"Desloca as linhas por uma distância especificada. Distâncias positivas "
"deslocarão as linhas à esquerda e distâncias negativas deslocarão as linhas "
"à direita."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4286
msgid "In blue the source layer, in red the offset one"
msgstr "Em azul a camada de origem, em vermelho a de deslocamento"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4292
msgid ":ref:`qgisarrayoffsetlines`, :ref:`qgistranslategeometry`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisarrayoffsetlines`, :ref:`qgistranslategeometry`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4316
msgid ""
"Offset distance. You can use the Data Defined button on the right to choose "
"a field from which the radius will be calculated. This way you can have "
"different radius for each feature (see :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`)."
msgstr ""
"Distância de desvio. Você pode usar o botão de definidor de data à direita "
"para escolher o campo do qual o raio será calculado. Dessa maneira, você "
"pode ter diferentes raios para cada característica (veja "
":ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4325
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6323
msgid "Default: 8"
msgstr "Padrão: 8"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4388
msgid "Output (offset) line layer"
msgstr "Saída (desvio) da linha de camada"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4393
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:offsetline``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:offsetline``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4403
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4413
msgid "Oriented minimum bounding box"
msgstr "Orientação mínima da caixa limitante."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4404
msgid ""
"Calculates the minimum area rotated rectangle for each feature in the input "
"layer."
msgstr ""
"Calcula a área mínima do retângulo rotacionado para cada feição na camada de"
" entrada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4437
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4460
msgid "**Bounding boxes**"
msgstr "**Bounding boxes**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4471
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orientedminimumboundingbox``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orientedminimumboundingbox``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4481
msgid "Orthogonalize"
msgstr "Ortogonalizar"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4482
msgid ""
"Attempts to orthogonalize the geometries of the input line or polygon layer."
" This process shifts the vertices in the geometries to try to make every "
"angle in the geometry either a right angle or a straight line."
msgstr ""
"Tentativas de ortoganalizar as geometrias das linhas de entrada ou camadas "
"poligonais. Esse processo muda os vértices das geometrias para tentar fazer "
"todo ângulo na geometria um ângulo reto ou uma linha reta."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4490
msgid "In blue the source layer and in the red orthogonalized result"
msgstr "Em azul a camada de origem e em vermelho o resultado ortogonalizado"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4513
msgid "**Maximum angle tolerance (degrees)**"
msgstr "**Tolerância máxima do ângulo (graus)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4514
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4604
msgid "``ANGLE_TOLERANCE``"
msgstr "``ANGLE_TOLERANCE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4518
msgid ""
"Specify the maximum deviation from a right angle or straight line a vertex "
"can have for it to be adjusted. Smaller tolerances mean that only vertices "
"which are already closer to right angles will be adjusted, and larger "
"tolerances mean that vertices which deviate further from right angles will "
"also be adjusted."
msgstr ""
"Especifique o desvio máximo de um ângulo reto ou uma linha reta que um "
"vértice pode ter para ser ajustado. Tolerâncias menores significam que "
"somente os vértices que já estão mais próximos dos ângulos retos serão "
"ajustados, e tolerâncias maiores significam que vértices com desvios mais "
"direcionados aos ângulos retos serão ajustados."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4524
msgid "**Maximum algorithm iterations**"
msgstr "**Maximum algorithm iterations**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4525
msgid "``MAX_ITERATIONS``"
msgstr "``MAX_ITERATIONS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4528
msgid "Default: 1000"
msgstr "Padrão: 1000"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4529
msgid ""
"Setting a larger number for the maximum number of iterations will result in "
"a more orthogonal geometry at the cost of extra processing time."
msgstr ""
"Configurando um número maior para o número máximo de iterações resultará em "
"uma geometria mais ortogonal ao custo de um maior tempo de processamento. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4532
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4555
msgid "**Orthogonalized**"
msgstr "**Ortogonalizado**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4558
msgid "The output polygon vector layer with adjusted angles."
msgstr "A camada vetorial de polígono de saída com ângulos ajustados."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4563
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orthogonalize``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orthogonalize``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4573
msgid "Point on Surface"
msgstr "Ponto na Superfície"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4574
msgid ""
"For each feature of the input layer, returns a point that is guaranteed to "
"lie on the surface of the feature geometry."
msgstr ""
"Para cada feição da camada de entrada, retorna um ponto que está garantido "
"na superfície da geometria da feição."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4585
msgid ":ref:`qgiscentroids`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgiscentroids`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4603
msgid "**Create point on surface for each part**"
msgstr "**Criar um ponto na superfície para cada parte**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4606
msgid "If checked, a point will be created for each part of the geometry."
msgstr "Se checado, um ponto será criado para parte da geometria."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4607
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4630
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4870
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4893
msgid "**Point**"
msgstr "**Ponto**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4633
msgid "The output point vector layer."
msgstr "A camada vetorial de ponto de saída "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4638
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointonsurface``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointonsurface``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4648
msgid "Points along geometry"
msgstr "Pontos ao longo da geometria"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4649
msgid ""
"Creates points at regular intervals along line or polygon geometries. "
"Created points will have new attributes added for the distance along the "
"geometry and the angle of the line at the point."
msgstr ""
"Cria pontos em intervalos regulares ao longo da linha ou geometrias "
"poligonais. Pontos criados irão ter novos atributos adicionados pela "
"distância ao longo da geometria e do angulo da linha no ponto."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4653
msgid ""
"An optional start and end offset can be specified, which controls how far "
"from the start and end of the geometry the points should be created."
msgstr ""
"Um começo opcional e fim do desvio pode especificar quais controles o quão "
"longes do começo e o final da geometria dos pontos deverão ser criados. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4660
msgid "Points created along the source line layer"
msgstr "Pontos criados ao longo da camada da linha de origem"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4665
msgid ":ref:`qgisinterpolatepoint`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisinterpolatepoint`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4688
msgid "Distance between two consecutive points along the line"
msgstr "Distância entre dois pontos consecutivos ao longo da linha"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4689
msgid "**Start offset**"
msgstr "**Start offset**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4690
msgid "``START_OFFSET``"
msgstr "``START_OFFSET``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4694
msgid ""
"Distance from the beginning of the input line, representing the position of "
"the first point."
msgstr ""
"Distância do início da linha de entrada, representando a posição do primeiro"
" ponto."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4696
msgid "**End offset**"
msgstr "**End offset**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4697
msgid "``END_OFFSET``"
msgstr "``END_OFFSET``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4738
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointsalonglines``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointsalonglines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4748
msgid "Points displacement"
msgstr "Deslocamento de pontos"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4749
msgid ""
"Given a distance of proximity, identifies nearby point features and radially"
" distributes them over a circle whose center represents their barycenter. A "
"convenient tool to scatter overlaid features."
msgstr ""
"Dada uma distância de proximidade, identifica feições de pontos próximos e "
"as distribui radialmente sobre um círculo cujo centro representa seu "
"baricentro. Uma ferramenta conveniente para espalhar feições sobrepostas."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4770
msgid "**Minimum distance to other points**"
msgstr "**Distância mínima para outros pontos**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4771
msgid "``PROXIMITY``"
msgstr "``PROXIMITY``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4775
msgid ""
"Distance below which point features are considered close. Close features are"
" distributed altogether."
msgstr ""
"Distância entre cada ponto das características são considerados próximos. "
"Características próxiumas são distribuídas completamente."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4778
msgid "**Displacement distance**"
msgstr "**Distância de deslocamento**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4783
msgid "Radius of the circle on which close features are placed"
msgstr "Raio do círculo no qual as feições próximas são colocadas"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4784
msgid "**Horizontal distribution for two point case**"
msgstr "**Distribuição horizontal para caso de dois pontos**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4785
msgid "``HORIZONTAL``"
msgstr "``HORIZONTAL``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4789
msgid ""
"When only two points are identified as close, aligns them horizontally on "
"the circle instead of vertically."
msgstr ""
"Quando apenas dois pontos são identificados como próximos, alinha-os "
"horizontalmente no círculo em vez de verticalmente."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4792
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4815
msgid "**Displaced**"
msgstr "**Deslocado**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4818
msgid "Output point vector layer"
msgstr "Camada vetorial de ponto de saída"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4823
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:pointsdisplacement``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:pointsdisplacement``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4833
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4846
msgid "Pole of inaccessibility"
msgstr "Pólo de inacessibilidade"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4834
msgid ""
"Calculates the pole of inaccessibility for a polygon layer, which is the "
"most distant internal point from the boundary of the surface."
msgstr ""
"Calcula o pole de inacessibilidade de uma camada poligonal, a qual é a mais "
"distante internamente do ponto do limite da superfície. "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4837
msgid ""
"This algorithm uses the 'polylabel' algorithm (Vladimir Agafonkin, 2016), "
"which is an iterative approach guaranteed to find the true pole of "
"inaccessibility within a specified tolerance. A more precise tolerance "
"(lower value) requires more iterations and will take longer to calculate."
msgstr ""
"Esse algoritmo usa o algoritmo \"polylabel\" (Vladimir Agafonkin, 2016) o "
"qual é uma abordagem iterativa garantida de achar o polo verdadeiro de "
"inacessibilidade dentro de uma tolerância especificada. Uma tolerância mais "
"precisa (valor baixo) requere mais iterações e levara mais tempo para "
"calcular."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4869
msgid "Set the tolerance for the calculation"
msgstr "Estabelecer a tolerância para o cálculo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4903
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:poleofinaccessibility``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:poleofinaccessibility``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4913
msgid "Polygonize"
msgstr "Poligonizar"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4914
msgid ""
"Creates a polygon layer whose features boundaries are generated from a line "
"layer of **closed** features."
msgstr ""
"Cria uma camada de polígono cujos limites de feições são gerados a partir de"
" uma camada de linha de feições **fechadas**."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4920
msgid "The yellow polygons generated from the closed lines"
msgstr "Os polígonos amarelos gerados a partir das linhas fechadas"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4922
msgid ""
"The line layer must have closed shapes in order to be transformed into a "
"polygon."
msgstr ""
"A camada de linha deve ter formas fechadas para ser transformada em um "
"polígono."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4925
msgid ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4943
msgid "**Keep fields from the input layer**"
msgstr "**Manter campos da camada de entrada**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4944
msgid "``KEEP_FIELDS``"
msgstr "``KEEP_FIELDS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4948
msgid ""
"Check to keep the fields (only the table structure, not the values) of the "
"input layer"
msgstr ""
"Check para manter os campos (somente a tabela de estrutura, não os valores) "
"da camada de entrada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4949
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4972
msgid "**Polygons from lines**"
msgstr "**Polígonos de linhas**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4975
msgid "The output polygon vector layer from lines"
msgstr "A camada vetorial de polígono de saída das linhas"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4981
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:polygonize``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:polygonize``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4991
msgid "Polygons to lines"
msgstr "Polígonos para linhas"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4992
msgid ""
"Takes a polygon layer and creates a line layer, with lines representing the "
"boundaries of the polygons in the input layer."
msgstr ""
"Pega uma camada de polígono e cria uma camada de linha, com linhas "
"representando os limites dos polígonos na camada de entrada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5001
msgid "Black lines as the result of the algorithm"
msgstr "Linhas pretas como resultado do algoritmo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5005
msgid ""
":ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5023
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5046
msgid "**Lines**"
msgstr "**Linhas**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5049
msgid "The output line vector layer from polygons"
msgstr "A camada vetorial de linha de saída de polígonos"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5054
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:polygonstolines``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:polygonstolines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5064
msgid "Project points (Cartesian)"
msgstr "Projetar pontos (Cartesiano)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5065
msgid ""
"Projects point geometries by a specified distance and bearing (azimuth)."
msgstr ""
"Projeta geometrias de pontos por uma distância e direção especificadas "
"(azimute)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5087
msgid "**Bearing (degrees from North)**"
msgstr "**Bearing (degrees from North)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5088
msgid "``BEARING``"
msgstr "``BEARING``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5092
msgid "Clockwise angle starting from North, in degree (°) unit"
msgstr "Ângulo no sentido horário a partir do Norte, em unidade de grau (°)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5098
msgid "Distance to offset geometries, in layer units"
msgstr "Distância das geometrias dos desvios, in unidades por camada"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5099
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5122
msgid "**Projected**"
msgstr "**Projetado**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5125
msgid "The output (projected) point vector layer"
msgstr "A camada vetorial de ponto de saída (projetada)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5130
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:projectpointcartesian``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:projectpointcartesian``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5140
msgid "Promote to multipart"
msgstr "Promover para multipartes"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5141
msgid ""
"Takes a vector layer with singlepart geometries and generates a new one in "
"which all geometries are multipart."
msgstr ""
"Pega uma camada vetorial com geometrias de uma única parte e gera uma nova "
"na qual todas as geometrias são multipartes."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5144
msgid ""
"Input features which are already multipart features will remain unchanged."
msgstr ""
"As feições de entrada que já são feições multipartes permanecerão "
"inalteradas."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5147
msgid ""
"This algorithm can be used to force geometries to multipart types in order "
"to be compatible with data providers that require multipart features."
msgstr ""
"Este algoritmo pode ser usado para forçar geometrias para tipos multipartes "
"para serem compatíveis com provedores de dados que requerem feições "
"multipartes."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5174
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5197
msgid "**Multiparts**"
msgstr "**Multipartes**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5200
msgid "The output multipart vector layer"
msgstr "A camada vetorial multipartes de saída"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5205
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:promotetomulti``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:promotetomulti``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5215
msgid "Rectangles, ovals, diamonds"
msgstr "Retângulos, ovais, diamantes"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5216
msgid ""
"Creates a buffer area with a rectangle, oval or diamond shape for each "
"feature of the input point layer."
msgstr ""
"Cria uma área de buffer com uma forma retangular, oval ou diamante para cada"
" feição da camada de ponto de entrada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5219
msgid ""
"The shape parameters can be fixed for all features or dynamic using a field "
"or an expression."
msgstr ""
"Os parâmetros de forma podem ser corrigidos para todas as feições ou "
"dinâmicos usando um campo ou uma expressão."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5225
msgid "Different buffer shapes with dynamic parameters"
msgstr "Diferentes formas de buffer com parâmetros dinâmicos"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5243
msgid "**Buffer shape**"
msgstr "**Buffer shape**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5244
msgid "``SHAPE``"
msgstr "``SHAPE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5246
msgid "The shape to use. One of:"
msgstr "A forma a ser usada. Uma de:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5248
msgid "0 --- Rectangles"
msgstr "0 --- Retângulos"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5249
msgid "1 --- Ovals"
msgstr "1 --- Ovais"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5250
msgid "2 --- Diamonds"
msgstr "2 --- Diamantes"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5252
msgid "**Width**"
msgstr "**Largura**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5257
msgid "Width of the buffer shape"
msgstr "Largura da forma do buffer"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5258
msgid "**Height**"
msgstr "**Altura**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5259
msgid "``HEIGHT``"
msgstr "``HEIGHT``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5263
msgid "Height of the buffer shape"
msgstr "Altura da forma do buffer"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5264
msgid "**Rotation**"
msgstr "**Rotação**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5267
msgid "``ROTATION``"
msgstr "``ROTATION``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5271
msgid "Rotation of the buffer shape"
msgstr "Rotação da forma do buffer"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5276
msgid "Default: 36"
msgstr "Padrão: 36"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5277
msgid "Number of segments for a full circle (*Ovals* shape)"
msgstr "Número de segmentos para um círculo completo (forma *Ovais*)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5278
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5301
msgid "**Output**"
msgstr "**Saída**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5304
msgid "The output vector layer (with the buffer shapes)"
msgstr "A camada vetorizada de saída (com shapes buffer)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5309
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:rectanglesovalsdiamonds``"
msgstr "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:rectanglesovalsdiamonds``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5319
msgid "Remove duplicate vertices"
msgstr "Remover vértices duplicados"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5320
msgid ""
"Removes duplicate vertices from features, wherever removing the vertices "
"does not result in a degenerate geometry."
msgstr ""
"Remove os vértices duplicados das feições, sempre que a remoção dos vértices"
" não resultar em uma geometria degenerada."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5323
msgid ""
"The tolerance parameter specifies the tolerance for coordinates when "
"determining whether vertices are identical."
msgstr ""
"O parâmetro de tolerância especifica a tolerância para coordenadas ao "
"determinar se os vértices são idênticos."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5326
msgid ""
"By default, Z values are not considered when detecting duplicate vertices. "
"E.g. two vertices with the same X and Y coordinate but different Z values "
"will still be considered duplicate and one will be removed. If the "
":guilabel:`Use Z Value` parameter is true, then the Z values are also tested"
" and vertices with the same X and Y but different Z will be maintained."
msgstr ""
"Por padrão, valores em Z não são considerados quando detectando vértices "
"duplicados, por exemplo, dois vértices com o mesmo X e Y de coordenada, mas "
"diferentes valores para Z ainda serão considerados duplicados e um será "
"removido. Se  a :guilabel:`Use Z Value`  for um parâmetro verdadeiro, então "
"os valores para Z também são testados e os vértices com o mesmo valor para X"
" e Y, mas diferentes para Z serão mantidos."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5337
msgid ""
"Duplicate vertices are not tested between different parts of a multipart "
"geometry, e.g. a multipoint geometry with overlapping points will not be "
"changed by this method."
msgstr ""
"Vértices duplicados não são testados entre diferentes partes de uma "
"geometria multipartes, por exemplo, uma geometria multiponto com pontos "
"sobrepostos não será alterada por este método."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5367
msgid "Vertices closer than the specified distance are considered duplicates"
msgstr ""
"Vértices mais próximos do que a distância especificada são considerados "
"duplicados"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5369
msgid "**Use Z value**"
msgstr "**Usar valor Z**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5370
msgid "``USE_Z_VALUE``"
msgstr "``USE_Z_VALUE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5374
msgid ""
"If the :guilabel:`Use Z Value` parameter is true, then the Z values are also"
" tested and vertices with the same X and Y but different Z will be "
"maintained."
msgstr ""
"Se o  :guilabel:`Use Z Value` parâmetro for verdadeiro, então os valores "
"para Z serão testados e os vértices com mesmo valor de X e Y  mas diferentes"
" para Z serão mantidos."

